news.title: Brihanmumbai civic body collects property tax of Rs 2,214 crore
news.para: The civic body collected Rs 9.51 crore property tax from the government-owned properties, it said. "Among the top 10 property owners whom the department pursued for collection of the tax was a private company from the S-ward in the eastern suburbs.

news.title: Bombay HC directs Navi Mumbai civic body to raze illegal building on CIDCO land
news.para: NNMC directed to demolish illegal building on CIDCO land in 8 weeks. No regularisation via fines/compensation. Private interests must align with public good. Structure built by Ishwar Mavji Patel.

news.title: Indore civic body receives single bid for 18,000 sq metre land
news.para: IMC additional commissioner Abhilash Mishra said that one firm from Indore submitted a bid with a demand draft of about Rs 1.59 crore, The base price of the property was set at Rs 31.80 crore.

news.title: Karl Lagerfeld's apartment in Paris sold for $10.8 million
news.para: Located in a 17th century building on Quai Voltaire, the three-room home has a view overlooking the Seine river and the Louvre Museum.

news.title: UK court allows sale of Nirav Modi's luxury London flat
news.para: The case involves Trident Trust Company (Singapore) Pte Limited as the claimant, seeking to sell its apartment asset in the Marylebone area of central London.

news.title: DDA initiates process to demolish Signature View Apartments in North Delhi
news.para: At the last hearing on the matter on March 14, Delhi High Court extended the interim stay against the demolition granted last year. The court also asked the Municipal Corporation of Delhi to explain the basis on which it declared Signature View Apartments dangerous.

news.title: India Cements plans to raise up to Rs 750 crore via bonds
news.para: The debt, which might be priced north of 15%, will be used to fund working capital and capital expenditure, said two sources aware of the development.

news.title: K Raheja inks pact to jointly develop 2.5-acre land parcel in Mumbai
news.para: The developer’s residential platform and the landlord have finalised a revenue share structure for the proposed joint development, wherein K Raheja Corp will get 57% revenue share, while the balance 43% will go to the landlord.

news.title: How this real estate goldmine in heart of Noida turned into a giant landfill
news.para: For six years, this plot lay with the Wave group, which built only on a slice of it – two towers that are yet to be completed – and eventually surrendered the rest to Noida Authority in 2017.

news.title: GOCL to monetise land parcel in Hyderabad for Rs 3,402 crore
news.para: The process will get completed over 18 months in carefully planned tranches, contingent upon the fulfilment of any associated covenants, it said, adding that R 520 crore will be received as the first instalment under the pact.

news.title: Vietnam jails luxury property tycoon over $355 million bond scam
news.para: A top Vietnamese luxury property tycoon was sentenced to eight years in prison, state media said Wednesday, after he was accused of cheating thousands of investors in a $355 million bond scam.

news.title: Two bidders in talks to buy Germany's Galeria
news.para: Galeria, currently under supervision of the insolvency manager, had been seeking a new owner after being hit by problems at Signa, the Austrian-based property empire that has become the biggest casualty so far in Europe's real-estate crisis.

news.title: China's Country Garden hires Kroll to carry out liquidation analysis: Sources
news.para: China's biggest private developer is facing a liquidation petition for non-payment of a $205 million loan, with a court hearing in the case set for May 17.

news.title: BigBloc Building Elements receive eligibility certificate for Rs 27.14 crore subsidy
news.para: In April 2023, Bigbloc Building Elements completed the first phase of Wada project by establishing 2.5 lakhs cubic meters per annum capacity of the AAC block.

news.title: South Korea prepares financial support for builders
news.para: The government, together with commercial banks, plans to provide 40.6 trillion won ($30.3 billion) of financial support for small and medium-sized companies through loan guarantees and lower interest rates from April.

news.title: Germany’s Aroundtown posts net loss of $2.64 billion in 2023
news.para: On Tuesday the MDax-listed company announced the suspension of its dividend due to market uncertainties and a focus on cash preservation.

news.title: Haryana DC calls meeting over installation of gates in residential societies
news.para: The district administration has received applications from RWAs of several housing colonies in new sectors and other areas of the city citing security problems.

news.title: Kanodia Group to invest over Rs 5,000 crore in real estate by 2028
news.para: Gautam Kanodia, co-founder, Kanodia Group said, "Initially focusing on projects in NCR, we aim to expand our real estate footprint to other regions as well."

news.title: Indore civic body to auction land worth Rs 23 crore starting March 27
news.para: The bids, with a base price of Rs 31.80 crore, will be opened on Wednesday evening after 5 pm. Experts expect that the market value of the land is significantly higher than the collector's guideline.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing accept bids worth $350 million for dollar-denominated social bonds
news.para: Indiabulls Housing Finance intends to use the proceeds from this for onward lending. Coupon rate is 9.70 per cent.
